Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui

Class TabrisUIEntryPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui.TabrisUIEntryPoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.eclipse.rap.rwt.application.EntryPoint
    public class TabrisUIEntryPoint
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.rap.rwt.application.EntryPoint, java.io.Serializable

    The TabrisUIEntryPoint class should be used as the EntryPoint for TabrisUI based applications. This is an implementation of the RWT interface EntryPoint which should be registered within an ApplicationConfiguration. It has no no-argument constructor. This means it can't be registered as a normalEntryPoint. Instead it should be registered with a EntryPointFactory. You don't need to implement this factory yourself, just use TabrisUIEntrypointFactory.

    The TabrisUIEntryPoint acts as a convenience class to avoid the need to implement an EntryPoint. Anyway, if you have the need to create your own display e.g. for using it together with JFace DataBinding, you need to create the TabrisUI by your own.

    Since:
    1.0
